#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:1
msgid "For Development"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:3
msgid ""
"_Does the code do the right thing — including on error, concurrent, and hot "
"paths — and is it proven by tests?_"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:5
msgid ""
"This is the index of the **development** guidelines. Each subsection is its "
"own page, and each entry below links a stable `short-name` to its guideline, "
"with a one-line gist so a reader (or a review tool) can grasp the guideline "
"before opening it."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:10
msgid "Index"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:12
msgid "**[Correctness](correctness.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:13
msgid ""
"[`checked-arithmetic`](correctness.md#checked-arithmetic): Use checked or "
"saturating arithmetic where overflow is possible; don't rely on wrapping."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:14
msgid ""
"[`debug-assert`](correctness.md#debug-assert): Invariants that should never "
"fail in correct code go in `debug_assert!`, not `assert!`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:15
msgid ""
"[`propagate-errors`](correctness.md#propagate-errors): Propagate errors with "
"`?`; don't `.unwrap()` where failure is legitimate."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:17
msgid "**[Concurrency](concurrency.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:18
msgid ""
"[`lock-ordering`](concurrency.md#lock-ordering): Establish and document one "
"global, hierarchical lock order to avoid deadlock."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:19
msgid ""
"[`no-io-under-spinlock`](concurrency.md#no-io-under-spinlock): Never do I/O "
"or blocking work under a spinlock; drop it first or use a sleeping mutex."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:20
msgid ""
"[`careful-atomics`](concurrency.md#careful-atomics): Use a lock when fields "
"change in concert; atomics only for a genuinely independent value."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:21
msgid ""
"[`atomic-critical-sections`](concurrency.md#atomic-critical-sections): Keep "
"a check-then-act sequence under one lock acquisition (else a TOCTOU race)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:23
msgid "**[Resource Management](resource-management.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:24
msgid ""
"[`raii`](resource-management.md#raii): Acquire and release every resource "
"via `Drop`, not manual enable/disable pairs."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:26
msgid "**[Efficiency](efficiency.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:27
msgid ""
"[`no-linear-hot-paths`](efficiency.md#no-linear-hot-paths): Keep hot paths "
"(syscall dispatch, scheduler enqueue) sub-linear; reject O(n) over large n."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:28
msgid ""
"[`minimize-copies`](efficiency.md#minimize-copies): Avoid needless copies/"
"allocations — cloning an `Arc` where a reference suffices, etc."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:29
msgid ""
"[`no-premature-optimization`](efficiency.md#no-premature-optimization): "
"Justify optimizations with measured data; don't add complexity for a non-"
"problem."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:31
msgid "**[Observability](observability.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:32
msgid ""
"[`ostd-log-only`](observability.md#ostd-log-only): Use the `ostd::log` "
"macros in OSTD-based crates, not the `log` crate directly."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:33
msgid ""
"[`log-levels`](observability.md#log-levels): Match the eight severity levels "
"to meaning — `error!` for recoverable failures, `emerg!` before halt."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:34
msgid ""
"[`log-prefix`](observability.md#log-prefix): Define a crate `__log_prefix` "
"at the crate root before any `mod`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:36
msgid "**[Testing](testing.md)**"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:37
msgid ""
"[`add-regression-tests`](testing.md#add-regression-tests): Every bug fix "
"ships a test that would have caught it, referencing the issue."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:38
msgid ""
"[`test-visible-behavior`](testing.md#test-visible-behavior): Test observable "
"behavior through public APIs; name tests after behavior, not internals."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:39
msgid ""
"[`use-assertions`](testing.md#use-assertions): Use assertion macros (clear "
"failure messages), not print-and-eyeball."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:40
msgid ""
"[`test-cleanup`](testing.md#test-cleanup): Clean up after every test (fds, "
"temp files, child processes) to avoid flakiness."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-development/index.md:42
msgid "No **path-specific** guidelines yet."
msgstr ""
